    ],
    "source": {
      "file": "[CE] questions.pdf",
      "exam": "K-Companies",
      "year": 2016,
      "tier": "gold",
      "originalNumber": 59
    },
    "keyProvenance": "answer_page",
    "flags": [],
    "keyVerified": true,
    "needsReview": false,
    "dedupeHash": "25de8b0fb7733bb53d71fc3ed3156cbb656de2b6",
    "explanation": "The physical layer is the only layer that touches the medium: it converts the bit stream into electrical, optical or electromagnetic signals and defines voltages, timing and connectors. Data Link works on frames of bits, not on signals."
  },
  {
    "id": "ce2016-q060",
    "type": "mcq",
    "topic": "networking",
    "subtopic": "osi-layers",
    "stem": "Which of the following is the main function of transport layer?",
    "options": [
      {
        "label": "A",
        "text": "Node to node delivery.",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "B",
        "text": "End to end delivery.",
        "isCorrect": true
      },
      {
        "label": "C",
        "text": "Maintaining routing tables.",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "D",
        "text": "None of the above.",
        "isCorrect": false
      }
    ],
    "answerOptionLabels": [
      "B"
    ],
    "source": {
      "file": "[CE] questions.pdf",
      "exam": "K-Companies",
      "year": 2016,
      "tier": "gold",
      "originalNumber": 60
    },
    "keyProvenance": "answer_page",
    "flags": [],
    "keyVerified": true,
    "needsReview": false,
    "dedupeHash": "ef3c9209e58f04546c697b9e8a39256d21a86f77",
    "explanation": "The transport layer's job is end-to-end (process-to-process) delivery: it takes the message from the sending process and delivers it to the receiving process, regardless of how many hops lie between. Node-to-node delivery is the data link layer and maintaining routing tables is the network layer, which are the two distractors."
  },
  {
    "id": "ce2016-q061",
    "type": "mcq",
    "topic": "networking",
    "subtopic": "osi-layers",
